#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=That ’s related actually to the next question .
#Text=You have a separate forum for discussion .
#Text=And the forum not only has discussion on the comic but has , ah serious business and news and sections for math and science and pretty much a lot different things .
#Text=So how is that ?
#Text=Whats your experience with the forums fora , and related to that what made you decide to add the additional , you know , topical to xkcd but more tangential .
#Text=If you could comment more directly on what the thought process is there ?
#Text=RM : I ’m less involved in the forums than some other people .
#Text=Davean is in the business with me is running the forums with me , and my old roommate Belial .

#Text=I had n’t thought of the IRC readers as potentially different from the forum readers so I ’m wondering if other than the obvious connection , aside from the obvious correlation you ’re going to get from IRC being more technical , a little more difficult to use obviously .
#Text=Have you noticed any other differences in the types of people on IRC as opposed to the forum users .
#Text=RM : Really I feel they ’re pretty similar .
#Text=I would n’t say that it 's more difficult or that there is a higher barrier of entry .
#Text=We get just as many dumb people on IRC as we get on the forums .
#Text=Just as many trolls or people wandering in .
#Text=Every community has its trouble causers and the really good people and everyone sort of mixing .
#Text=I do n’t think that the demographics are all that different really .
#Text=It 's just a matter of which medium you ’ve had more experience with and are more comfortable in .
#Text=You also have your " blag " which is really a blog .
#Text=( Comic 148 Mispronouncing )
#Text=What about that ?
#Text=RM .
#Text=The blag is a fun thing .
#Text=A project for me .
#Text=as for the community on the blag , I do n’t think there ’s much of a community .
#Text=There are people who read it , mainly when it gets linked to by something .

#Text=There are people who are reading it and commenting but they generally are talking back and forth to me , they ’re not talking to each other as much so I feel like that ’s just a place to talk about interesting , science technology and funny things .
#Text=There have n’t been a lot of posts so far .
#Text=It 's sort of a young thing so we ’re sort of waiting to see where that goes .
#Text=What ’s your favorite xkcd comic ?
#Text=RM : There are some , ones where I feel like I got things right .
#Text=I ’ve always liked the ball-pit one .
#Text=Hearing about how people like it and how people respond to it makes me like it even more .

#Text=There have been a lot of new ones where it would be easier to name , but the ones that have been around long enough people have really responded to way back when the answer to this was the comic about the MC Hammer slide , and I liked that one .
#Text=I feel that one worked out pretty well .
#Text=There have been a lot in the last year or so , last 6th months that where I felt I got things right .
#Text=The one with the internet map made it all over the place , and since then there have been a few where they ’ve been so well-reviewed that I think of them as high points of the strip .
#Text=But I do n’t know ; I have soft spot that ’s sort for the silliness of some of them .
